      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;Spell sets?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;I can see where it would be useful to have a pre-chosen set of spells for different purposes set and ready to go.  After all, I had just started playing with the Bandolier function for the Primary/Secondary/Range choices because I thought it might be useful to have my minor haste item from the tutorial in the Range slot while running, and then revert back to my Festive Doll for everything else.  So, I mentioned to a friend with whom I was adventuring that I wished there were a Spell Bandolier just like the equipment one; that way, I could do pre-adventure buffing, and then be able to switch to spells more suitable for debuffing/attacking (without having to laboriously sit down and &amp;quot;forget&amp;quot;/memorize them all).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;So, how do I set up such spell sets?  I'm only a level 12 (right now, probably a 13 with a couple more adventures), thus I don't have the same choices as someone of higher levels.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Verdana"&gt;And when I'm doing solo stuff, at least one slot has to be my Gate; I really hate the hassle of dying.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
